Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibria of the 1,1,1-Trifluoroethane + n-Butane System
Citation.sAbstract: Binary vapor-liquid equilibrium data were measured for the 1,1,1-trifluoroethane (HFC-143a) + n-butane  (HC-600) system at temperatures from (313.15 to 363.15) K. This experiment was carried out with a circulatingtype  apparatus with online gas chromatography. The experimental data were correlated well by Peng-Robinson-  Stryjek-Vera equation of state with the Wong-Sandler mixing rules. The average absolute deviation of pressure  and vapor composition between the measured data and the correlation was below 0.98 % and 0.0128, respectively.
